case.name: Stroke warning signs (info)
case.message: What are the warning signs of stroke?

results.chat_reply:
Warning signs of stroke (act FAST):

FAST:
- F: Face drooping
- A: Arm weakness (one side)
- S: Speech difficulty (slurred / unable to speak)
- T: Time to call emergency services immediately

Other possible warning signs:
- Sudden numbness or weakness (especially one side)
- Sudden confusion or trouble understanding
- Sudden trouble seeing in one or both eyes
- Sudden severe headache (worst headache) with no known cause
- Sudden trouble walking, dizziness, loss of balance/coordination

What to do right now:
- Call emergency services immediately
- Note the time symptoms started (or last known well)
- Do not wait for symptoms to improve
